entries.title: How will US Republicans manage the House over the next two years?
entries.description: Kevin McCarthy won the role of speaker of the House of Representatives in the US after 15 rounds of voting.

entries.title: Ukraine denies Russian claim it killed hundreds of soldiers
entries.description: Moscow said its 'retaliatory strike' killed more than 600 soldiers, but Kyiv said its armed forces were not affected.

entries.title: Jair Bolsonaro supporters storm Brazil’s Congress
entries.description: Hundreds of supporters breached the Congress and also gathered near the presidential palace and Supreme Court.

entries.title: UK PM Sunak signals he is open to discussing pay rises for nurses
entries.description: Rishi Sunak is under pressure to improve wage offers to healthcare staff amid a wave of industrial action over wages.

entries.title: Sweden says cannot fulfil Turkey’s demands for NATO application
entries.description: Prime Minister Ulf Kristersson says Turkey asking for too much, but is confident Ankara will approve its bid for NATO.

entries.title: Powerful earthquake hits Vanuatu, triggers tsunami warning
entries.description: Tsunami warning issued for parts of the South Pacific Ocean region after 7.0 magnitude quake hits Vanuatu.

entries.title: More than 20 killed in bus crash near Kenya-Uganda border
entries.description: Twenty-one killed and 49 others injured, police say, in incident that occurred after driver lost control of a bus.

entries.title: Al-Aqsa storming doesn’t bode well for religious rights in Israel
entries.description: Ben-Gvir's actions are a direct threat not just to Muslims, but also Christians and liberal Jews.

entries.title: Barbara Walters and the curse of celebrity journalism
entries.description: Although Walters has been celebrated as a pioneer, she has contributed much to undermining the journalistic profession.

entries.title: NATO turns down Serbia’s request to deploy troops in Kosovo

entries.title: Deq: The tattooist preserving the ink of a disappearing culture

entries.title: Dozens killed after buses collide in central Senegal

entries.title: Pakistan’s finance minister to meet IMF delegation in Geneva
entries.description: IMF has yet to approve the release of $1.1bn originally due to be disbursed in November last year.

entries.title: Israel revokes entry permits of senior Palestinian officials

entries.title: Man arrested after urinating on woman on board Air India flight

entries.title: Ukraine sanctions dozens of Russian artists, public figures

entries.title: Russia-Ukraine war: List of key events, day 319

entries.title: Benin holds parliamentary vote, the opposition is allowed to run

entries.title: China reopens borders to quarantine-free travel
